<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,310,1585,1611]" box="[189,310,1585,1611]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1585,1611]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1585,1611]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[189,1399,1632,1834]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
This species is recognized among species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hwang &amp; Weirauch, 2017" authorityName="Hwang &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2017" box="[718,926,1632,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Macrophysoderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[718,926,1632,1658]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Macrophysoderes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[934,1041,1632,1658]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the dark brown coloration, the scape reaching the apex of the clypeus, the very large eyes relative to the head, the absence of paired long setae at the posterior margin of the postocular lobe, the two rows of small setigerous tubercles on the ventral surface of the postocular lobe, the pronotum with deep paramedian carinae, the triangular pronotal paramedian lobes, the spines on the fore trochanter and the straight margin of the abdominal apex. This species is quite distinct from other members of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
