</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[189,793,313,339]" box="[189,793,313,339]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Nothing is known about the biology of this species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="40.[189,342,379,405]" box="[189,342,379,405]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,342,379,405]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,379,405]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[189,1398,425,487]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
This species is only known from two localities: Pusa, Bengal (
<typeStatus box="[915,967,425,451]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">type</typeStatus>
locality) and Khasia Hills, Assam. It appears to be restricted to areas adjoining the Indian subcontinent and 
<collectingCountry box="[1016,1132,461,487]" name="Myanmar" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="40.[189,303,526,552]" box="[189,303,526,552]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,526,552]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,526,552]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[189,1399,572,705]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
This species is placed in the 
<taxonomicName authority="Hwang &amp; Weirauch, 2017" authorityName="Hwang &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2017" box="[518,726,573,599]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Macrophysoderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[518,726,573,599]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Macrophysoderes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[732,838,573,599]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
clade based on the phylogenetic analysis above. It is most closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hwang &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Miller" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[520,677,608,634]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Macrophysoderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[520,677,608,634]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[686,819,608,634]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, as both possess a scape that reaches the apex of the clypeus and lack the paired, long setae at the posterior margin of the postocular lobe. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hwang &amp; Weirauch" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Hwang &amp; Weirauch" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[1222,1399,643,669]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Physoderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bengalensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1222,1399,643,669]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">M. bengalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,319,678,705]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
possesses several unique characters, especially on the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
